This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with a widely-used tool for binary classification, the Support Vector Machine (SVM), which is a supervised learning technique. The paper also proposes a new streaming SVM algorithm based on the minimum enclosing ball (MEB) problem, which is a well-known optimization problem in machine learning. 

The paper may also belong to the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it deals with the problem of designing efficient algorithms for processing large datasets in a streaming (online) setting, which requires sub-linear space. The paper proposes a new algorithm based on the blurred ball cover, which is a data structure used for efficient nearest neighbor search. 

The paper may also belong to the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as SVMs are widely used in computer vision for tasks such as object recognition, image classification, and face detection. The paper may also propose a new streaming SVM algorithm that is specifically designed for processing large-scale image datasets. 

The paper may also belong to the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as SVMs are a popular tool in the field of AI for tasks such as classification, regression, and anomaly detection.
